TITLE: Jim Cramer says he remains confident in U.S. economy despite Covid delta surge
SUMMARY: The "Mad Money" host said rosy outlooks from real estate investment trusts are a reassuring sign.

TITLE: Cramer urges investors to take profits in Robinhood as it becomes a meme stock
SUMMARY: The "Mad Money" host said investors in Robinhood needed to remain disciplined and trim their positions after the stock's massive two-day gains.

TITLE: Cramer says DuPont is an industrial 'bargain' as Wall Street misjudges the stock
SUMMARY: The "Mad Money" host said he wants investors to "see the opportunity in the industrial bargain bin before it disappears."

TITLE: Cramer says bet on these 'pseudo-lockdown stocks' as Wall Street worries about Covid delta variant
SUMMARY: The "Mad Money" host's list of stocks includes retailers such as Target and Costco, as well as delivery giants UPS and FedEx.

TITLE: Charts suggest the stock market is getting close to a near-term top, Cramer says
SUMMARY: "The charts, as interpreted by the legendary Tom DeMark, suggest that the market's getting close to a top, especially the S&P 500 and the Nasdaq 100," Jim Cramer said.

TITLE: Clorox CEO confident in growth prospects, even after disappointing quarter and guidance
SUMMARY: "If you look at the fundamentals of our business, our brands have never been stronger," Clorox CEO Linda Rendle told CNBC's Jim Cramer Tuesday.

TITLE: Cramer says Robinhood is a buy even after its rocky IPO
SUMMARY: The "Mad Money" host said the reaction to Square's planned Afterpay acquisition shows the benefits of Robinhood expanding into new services.

TITLE: Cramer says it is the 'height of irresponsibility' to invest in Chinese stocks right now
SUMMARY: "Mad Money" host Jim Cramer urged the show's viewers to forgo investments in Chinese stocks due to the uncertain regulatory environment.

TITLE: Charts suggest S&P 500 may struggle in August while gold looks set to rally, Cramer says
SUMMARY: "Mad Money" host Jim Cramer analyzes charts from technician Larry Williams that offer insight into how gold and the S&P 500 may trade this month.

TITLE: Jim Cramer says Carrier is a 'deliciously not sexy' stock investors can get behind
SUMMARY: "We spend a lot of time focused on exciting companies … it's often easier to make good money from boring companies like Carrier," the "Mad Money" host said.

TITLE: Robinhood CEO Vlad Tenev on stock's first-day decline: 'I'm used to being doubted'
SUMMARY: "We're building a long-term business, so you have to ignore these short-term fluctuations," said Robinhood CEO Vlad Tenev after shares fell 8% in its debut.

TITLE: Jim Cramer calls out the 'Jimmy Chill contrarians' who bet against Alphabet, AMD, and Boeing
SUMMARY: CNBC's Jim Cramer took a victory lap on the stocks of Alphabet, AMD, and Boeing after the companies reported better-than-expected quarterly results.

TITLE: Wingstop plans ghost kitchens in Manhattan as company leans on digital
SUMMARY: Wingstop plans to open 25 company-owned locations in Manhattan with about half of the spots dedicated to deliveries, CEO Charlie Morrison said.

TITLE: Jim Cramer advises investors to stay the course after Tuesday's decline
SUMMARY: "You have to remember that this prism could be temporary ... but I suspect the market is in fault-finding mode," the "Mad Money" host said.

TITLE: UPS CEO says U.S. deliveries slowed down last quarter as economy reopened
SUMMARY: E-commerce sales continue to boom, but the rate of growth has changed from a year ago when the U.S. was sheltering in place, UPS CEO Carol Tome said on CNBC.

TITLE: Jim Cramer sees a 'second reopening' trade in the recovery stocks
SUMMARY: "Once we start getting over this new outbreak, they'll be the place to invest," the "Mad Money" host said of travel, leisure, retail, energy and other stocks.

TITLE: Cramer says three restaurant stocks can outperform as Covid fears rise
SUMMARY: "These stocks are exactly what you want to own if the great reopening is hitting a delta variant-induced snag," the "Mad Money" host said.

TITLE: Cramer's week ahead: The most important week of earnings season
SUMMARY: "This is the toughest week of the quarter when it comes to making informed financial decisions," CNBC's Jim Cramer said ahead of reports from Apple and others.

TITLE: Jim Cramer says near-term Covid delta variant concerns won't threaten long-term stock market gains
SUMMARY: CNBC's Jim Cramer advised investors to keep a long-term focus in the face of Covid delta variant concerns.

TITLE: Domino’s CEO says return of late-night, weekend orders fueling sales growth during Covid reopening
SUMMARY: "Think about late-night business. Think about the weekend business .... It's coming back this year," Domino's Pizza CEO Ritch Allison told CNBC.

TITLE: Jim Cramer reacts to Chipotle big earnings beat: 'Chipotle delivered'
SUMMARY: "We always hear about these executives who say a crisis is a terrible thing to waste. Most of the time they're just blowing smoke. Not Chipotle," Cramer said.

TITLE: Jim Cramer predicts S&P 500 'is done getting slammed,' sees upside ahead
SUMMARY: "The charts, as interpreted by Carolyn Boroden, suggest that the S&P 500 is done getting slammed, with more upside ahead," the "Mad Money" host said.

TITLE: Biden says what others are 'afraid to say' about tech, Salesforce's Marc Benioff says
SUMMARY: As the White House gears up to challenge practices in the technology industry, Salesforce CEO said President Biden is "saying a lot of really smart things."

TITLE: Corporate earnings will dictate the market's next move, Jim Cramer says
SUMMARY: CNBC's Jim Cramer said the bond market gave stocks a reprieve on Tuesday, but the stock market will count on earnings to sustain its rebound from a big sell-off.

TITLE: Bed Bath and Beyond CEO says Casper partnership reflects company's new focus
SUMMARY: Bed Bath and Beyond CEO Mark Tritton told CNBC that it has partnered with sleep company Casper to solidify its hold on the bed and sleep products market.

TITLE: Jim Cramer says the stock market will bottom after speculators find the exit
SUMMARY: "Once the speculators are blown out … and the stocks that are already down huge start rallying, then we can find a tradeable bottom," the "Mad Money" host said.

TITLE: First Horizon regional bank reaps benefits of southern population growth, CEO says
SUMMARY: "We're seeing an influx of people into the South. It's been very, very positive, and we will continue to see that," First Horizon Bank CEO Bryan Jordan told CNBC.

TITLE: Jim Cramer says flood of IPOs is weighing on stock prices
SUMMARY: "Many stocks are getting hit here because there's not enough cash to buy all the junk that's been created of late," the "Mad Money" host said.

TITLE:
U.S. must invest in caregiving to stay competitive, Commerce Secretary Raimondo 
says
SUMMARY: Family care is keeping women out of the workforce and the U.S. must address it to remain competitive in the labor market, Commerce Secretary Gina Raimondo said.

TITLE: Delta, Apple, Best Buy are some stocks that will benefit from consumer spending rebound, Cramer says
SUMMARY: The corporate earnings season is under way, and CNBC's Jim Cramer thinks the early reports from major banks all have something in common.
